cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.SE, cs.FL

This paper discusses the formulation of induction and coinduction principles in programming languages and type theory, which are topics related to logic and semantics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). However, the paper also specifically focuses on PL (Programming Languages) type theory, which makes cs.PL (Programming Languages) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the potential relevance of these concepts to object-oriented programming (OOP), which could fall under cs.TL (Programming Languages and Compilers) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper briefly touches on the topic of fixed points, which could fall under cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory).
